1
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:00,400
Zhu Keke.

2
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:03,160
Zhu Keke,

3
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:05,650
where did she go?

4
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:06,960
Zhu Keke.

5
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:09,800
Could it be here?

6
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,240
Did she send the wrong location?

7
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:12,700
Let's go in and take a look.

8
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,080
Zhu Keke.

9
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:16,880
Zhu Keke.

10
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:25,880
Oh no. It won't open.

11
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:32,360
Oh no.

12
00:01:33,479 --> 00:01:35,479
Are we going to be trapped here?

13
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:37,560
We will find an exit.

14
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,890
There is light over there. Let's go check.

15
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,240
Zhu Keke.

16
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,479
Zhu Keke.

17
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,210
How do you have this?

18
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,320
Don't you know what I do for a living?

19
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:08,240
We're so unlucky together.

20
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,400
The door is stuck.

21
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,720
And my phone is dead.

22
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,960
Are you saying I'm a jinx?

23
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,600
Is anyone there?

24
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,320
Is anyone there?

25
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:23,800
Zhu Keke!

26
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,760
Is anyone there?

27
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,400
Is anyone there?

28
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:31,160
Zhu Keke!

29
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,800
There's a window.

30
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,480
Is anyone there? Help!

31
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,640
Is anyone there? Help!

32
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,960
This damn place.

33
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:53,000
I wonder if my cousin will come and save me.

34
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:54,440
Zhu Keke!

35
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,040
Zhu Keke!

36
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,080
Su Wan, where are you?

37
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,280
I'm already here.

38
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,490
Did you go the wrong way?

39
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:19,560
Is anyone there? Help!

40
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,840
Is anyone there? Help!

41
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,800
Is anyone there?

42
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,680
Help!

43
00:03:29,079 --> 00:03:29,880
Stop yelling.

44
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:32,800
No one will answer you even if you yell your lungs out.

45
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,040
We might as well figure out a way ourselves.

46
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:37,200
If we don't figure something out,

47
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,040
are we going to be trapped here forever?

48
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,160
And let me tell you,

49
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,240
I actually didn't pass out.

50
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,520
Am I cured?

51
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:13,640
Who is it?

52
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:22,200
Coming to my godforsaken warehouse in the middle of the night

53
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:22,760
looking for a thrill?

54
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,240
No, no, no.

55
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,720
It's not what you think.

56
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,100
Hurry up and leave.

57
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,690
It's quite dangerous here.

58
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,970
Your phone has a signal.

59
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,080
Hello?

60
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:36,960
What?

61
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:39,520
Got it.

62
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,260
They found the dog.

63
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:43,600
Really?

64
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,880
Let's go quickly then.

65
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:45,480
Let's go.

66
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,490
These young people.

67
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,200
Da Huo.

68
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,159
Da Huo.

69
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,960
Where did you go?

70
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,360
You have the nerve to ask?

71
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,440
Thanks to this guy,

72
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,370
not only did he find Keke for me,

73
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:04,560
but he also gave me a discount on the reward.

74
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,960
He only asked for 10,000.

75
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:08,560
Just doing a good deed.

76
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,240
The puppy is so cute.

77
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,480
Keke got lost right here.

78
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,720
Maybe Keke came back on its own.

79
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:15,840
Keke.

80
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,970
I saw the missing dog poster you put up.

81
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,720
I used all my connections to find it.

82
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:21,560
You're not thanking me,

83
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,960
but instead twisting the truth here.

84
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,160
Give the money back to her.

85
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:24,890
Why should I?

86
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,690
The dog got lost in our factory.

87
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,840
It's our duty to find it.

88
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,600
Aren't you meddling too much?

89
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:32,960
You wouldn't want me to check the factory's security footage, would you?

90
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,200
It's no big deal.

91
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:35,560
Let's not ruin our friendship.

92
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,080
Good brothers forever.

93
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:43,120
You deliberately let Keke go.

94
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:45,159
Because I study animal science,

95
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,240
from its... Stop.

96
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,170
I don't have time to listen to this.

97
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:49,980
How about this?

98
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:52,480
You pay the 3,000 I owe him,

99
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,730
and you keep the 7,000. How about that?

100
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:56,840
Deal.

101
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:57,480
Okay.

102
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,210
Then it's happily decided.

103
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:00,760
Alright.

104
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,960
Debt-free, we are both happy.

105
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,080
Keke.

106
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:06,800
Come.

107
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,320
It's finally resolved.

108
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:24,840
Su Wan.

109
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:27,000
I was inspired by a foreign paper.

110
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:28,480
I suggest that

111
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:30,160
after you find a boyfriend,

112
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,820
you can try exposure therapy.

113
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,680
Ex...

114
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,040
That means

115
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:38,040
trying to maintain long eye contact with him.

116
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,060
Holding hands,

117
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,280
holding hands,

118
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,600
or even kissing.

119
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:55,570
These are all

120
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,960
very effective auxiliary treatments.

121
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,960
Treatments.

122
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,200
Could he be my cure?

123
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,120
Hello.

124
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,240
Hello.

125
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:41,400
Can I ask you a favor?

126
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,000
What is it?

127
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:44,240
Well...

128
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,620
Bai Tianyu.

129
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,480
Be my boyfriend.

130
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,400
What?

131
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,800
You are my chosen antidote.

132
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,680
Are you crazy?

133
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,520
I have no time to play with you.

134
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,360
No, just say yes.

135
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,420
I'll do whatever you ask, really.

136
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,440
I can help you with a lot of things,

137
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:10,480
like running errands, grabbing tools,

138
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,280
fixing cars, cleaning up.

139
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,320
I can do it all.

140
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,540
Then hand me a flathead screwdriver.

141
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,080
Okay.

142
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,640
Is it this one?

143
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,880
This is a flathead screwdriver.

144
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,360
That's a Phillips.

145
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,720
You don't even know such basic stuff.

146
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,380
How can you do precision work?

147
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:47,120
I don't know it, but I can learn, really.

148
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:47,760
Besides,

149
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,200
my cousin Zhu Junchi,

150
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,000
he can get you countless orders.

151
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,820
You just need to be with me.

152
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,940
What kind of person do you take me for?

153
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:57,600
I don't know,

154
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:00,360
nor do I understand this 'chosen antidote' you mentioned.

155
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:02,360
I don't need or want a relationship.

156
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,760
Give up.

157
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,050
Don't bother me.

158
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,320
I didn't mean that.

159
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,400
How about...

160
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,600
Could you think about it again?

161
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:32,840
Hello.

162
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,600
Why do we have to date?
